@drag0 - That lib is tragically out of date with angular, hence the import issues. To the best of my knowledge, a good hashing lib doesn't exist.

If this were my issue, I would probably use ts-md5 as a starting point if portions of it are viable, include it in a shared module ( faster for developing ) and stick a comment at the top referencing the original repo. Once it's current & in good working order, PR it back to the original repo or publish a new package if the owner doesn't respond.

That said, it really has nothing to do with angular2 and if all else fails using crypto-js would take very little effort to wedge into an ng2 application.

